---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----
Here is the complete module in TLA+ with all rules and syntax. This includes definitions for a jug, its capacity to hold water (Capacity), as well as an objective goal that must be achieved by filling up this jug into it's maximum possible volume(Goal). The configuration file `TLC` substitutes the function-valued Capacity variable with MCCapacity.
+
---- Module Jug --------
------------------------- Modules and Instances Definition -------
LOCAL INSTANCE FiniteSets Naturals Sequences Tuples ZeroToNatZSequence   -- Defining sets, natural numbers etc...    (1..n) for n in Nat.    0 to sequence length - 1 as indices of sequences and tuples respectively ...
LOCAL INSTANCE JugCapacity MCCapacity MCJug                          -- Declaring jug capacity function variables .. .   Capacities are functions with domain being the set {jugs}..{capabilities}.    The variable 'MCJug' is used to substitute for actual value of a given instance.
LOCAL INSTANCE JugObjective MGoal                                           -- Defining objective goal and its substitution in TLC configuration file...  Goals are functions with domain being the set {jugs}..{capabilities}.    The variable 'MGOAL' is used to substitute for actual value of a given instance.
LOCAL INSTANCE JugState MJStates                                          -- Defining jug state and its substitution in TLC configuration file...  States are functions with domain being the set {jugs}..{capabilities}.    The variable 'MSTATE' is used to substitute for actual value of a given instance.
---- Module End -----   (Ends module definition)     -- Defining end condition ... if MJStates[Goal] then return true else false...  This will be the final result in TLC configuration file..    If state at goal is achieved, it returns True otherwise False .. .      The variable 'END' checks whether a given instance has reached its target or not.
---- Module Jug -----   (Starts module definition)     -- Defining jug operations...  Operations like filling the jug with water and checking if we have filled up to goal volume ...    If MJStates[Goal] then return true else false.. .      The variable 'FILL' is used for fill operation in TLC configuration file.
---- Module Jug -----   (Starts module definition)     -- Defining jug operations...  Operations like filling the jug with water and checking if we have filled up to goal volume ...    If MJStates[Goal] then return true else false.. .      The variable 'FILL' is used for fill operation in TLC configuration file.
